  "text": "β 0 is the mass-averaged flow turning of the reference blade and is here selected as the target. β is the flow turning on each cell face at the exit, which is computed as the inverse tangent of the tangential velocity to the axial velocity. A proper value of the coefficient Λ in front of the penalty function must be selected to enforce the exit flow turning constraint. The boundary conditions of the adjoint equation coupled with such a design objective were presented previously [CITATION_1] .",
